        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 17 at 3:14PM MDT until June 17 at 3:45PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>SVRGLD

The National Weather Service in Goodland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Cheyenne County in east central Colorado...

* Until 345 PM MDT.

* At 311 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles west of
Kit Carson, or 39 miles west of Cheyenne Wells, moving southeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail. Accumulating hail.

SOURCE...Spotters reported accumulating hail up to six inches in
depth with this storm. Additionally flooded roads and
washed out roads due to the heavy rain and accumulating
hail.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles and washed out roads is expected.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Cheyenne County in east central Colorado, including
the following locations... Aroya.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Prepare immediately for large hail and deadly cloud to ground
lightning. Seek shelter inside a well-built structure. Stay away
from windows.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
